"Here is a method in Java to convert a string to title case, while handling exception words like 'of', 'the', 'is', and 'and' appropriately:

```java
public class TitleCaseConverter {
    // List of exception words to be lowercase
    private static final List<String> EXCEPTION_WORDS = List.of("of", "the", "is", "and");

    /**
     * Converts a given string to title case, with exception words not capitalized unless they are the first word.
     * @param input The input string to be converted.
     * @return The converted string in title case.
     */
    public static String toTitleCase(String input) {
        if (input == null || input.isEmpty()) {
            return input;
        }

        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder();
        String[] words = input.split("\\s+");

        // Capitalize the first word
        if (words.length > 0) {
            result.append(Character.toUpperCase(words[0].charAt(0)));
            result.append(words[0].substring(1));
        }

        // Process remaining words
        for (int i = 1; i < words.length; i++) {
            String word = words[i];
            // Check if the word is an exception word
            if (ExceptionalWordChecker.isExceptionWord(word)) {
                result.append(word);
            } else {
                // Capitalize the first letter of the word
                result.append(Character.toUpperCase(word.charAt(0)));
                result.append(word.substring(1));
            }
        }

        return result.toString();
    }

    /**
     * Checks if a word is an exception word.
     * @param word The word to check.
     * @return true if the word is an exception word, false otherwise.
     */
    private static class ExceptionalWordChecker {
        public static boolean isExceptionWord(String word) {
            return EXCEPTION_WORDS.contains(word);
        }
    }
}
```

